As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 354 people, 145 households, and 94 families residing in the borough. The population density was {{convert|758.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 157 housing units at an average density of {{convert|336.6|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the borough was 98.59% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.85% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 0.56% from two or more races.

There were 145 households, out of which 30.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 55.2% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 4.8% had a female householder with no husband present, and 34.5% were non-families. 30.3% of all households were made up of individuals, and 11.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.44 and the average family size was 3.08.

In the borough the population was spread out, with 26.6% under the age of 18, 11.0% from 18 to 24, 28.0% from 25 to 44, 20.3% from 45 to 64, and 14.1% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 34 years. For every 100 females there were 114.5 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 101.6 males.

The median income for a household in the borough was $30,625, and the median income for a family was $38,438. Males had a median income of $27,813 versus $18,125 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the borough was $13,752. About 7.1% of families and 11.0% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 8.2% of those under age 18 and 17.8% of those age 65 or over.

